HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1048
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor Cooper Williams upon scoring more
than 1,000 points in his high school basketball
career.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should recognize those incredibly successful student
athletes who have distinguished themselves as inspirational leaders among their peers; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Williams of Smith County High School joined the 1,000-Point Club
for Tennessee high school basketball by scoring his 1,000th point against York Institute on
February 20, 2026; and
WHEREAS, no matter his path in life, Cooper Williams is an outstanding young man who
will continue to make a difference in his community, both on and off the court; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Williams's outstanding accomplishments are a great source of pride for
his family, his school, and the good people of Smith County; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Williams exemplifies the spirit, determination, and perseverance for
which Tennesseans are notable, and he is richly deserving of our approbation on this special
occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Cooper Williams upon joining the 1,000-Point
Club by scoring more than 1,000 points in his high school basketball career and wish him much
continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
